    <h1>Why this site exists</h1>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--tight">
  <div class="wrap wrap--narrow">
    <div class="prose">
      <p class="lead">
        I couldn't burp for most of my life. For years I didn't have a word for the bloating,
        the gurgling, and the pressure after every meal &mdash; I just assumed it was normal.
        It wasn't. It was RCPD, and it turned out to be treatable.
      </p>
      <p>
        After a single Botox injection, I burped for the first time. The symptoms that had
        quietly shaped my eating habits and social life for years mostly went away. The hardest
        part of the whole journey wasn't the treatment &mdash; it was finding out the condition
        existed and had a name at all.
      </p>
      <p>
        This site is my attempt to shorten that road for someone else. Everything here is free,
        has no ads, and asks for nothing in return. The goal is simple: help people recognize
        the symptoms, understand the science, and find a doctor who can help.
      </p>

      <h2>What you'll find here</h2>
      <ul class="stack">
        <li><a href="/diagnosis.html">A private self-check</a> to see how closely your symptoms match RCPD.</li>
        <li><a href="/research.html">Peer-reviewed research</a> and clinician talks you can bring to an appointment.</li>
        <li><a href="/find-a-doctor.html">A community-built directory</a> of doctors who diagnose and treat RCPD.</li>
        <li><a href="/faq.html">Plain-language answers</a> to the questions most people have at the start.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>With thanks</h2>
      <p>
        This site stands on the shoulders of the <a href="{{ site.reddit }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener">r/noburp</a>
        community, the clinicians researching RCPD, and the volunteers who built the doctor list.
        The anatomical illustrations are by
        <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/natalie_uic/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">u/natalie_uic</a>,
        and the original doctor directory was compiled with help from
        <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/karybrie/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">u/karybrie</a>.
      </p>

      <p class="callout callout--note">
        I'm not a doctor, and nothing here is medical advice. It's the resource I wish I'd had &mdash;
        a starting point for a conversation with a qualified professional.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
